cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR. 

This paper is about improving neural machine translation (NMT) by integrating a phrase memory from a phrase-based statistical machine translation (SMT) system. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which covers topics related to natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category as well. The proposed model is based on the encoder-decoder architecture, which falls under cs.LG (Learning) category. The paper also involves probability estimations, which is related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category. Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques, which is related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) category.
